# 📝 Nix Guidelines: Idioms for flakes, modules, and packages

> **Be explicit. Be reproducible. Be cross-platform.**

---

## 🧐 When?

- Writing/editing `flake.nix`
- Making Nix/NixOS/Home Manager modules
- Building Nix packages or overlays
- Reviewing Nix PRs/patches

---

## 🛑 No `with` Statements — Ever

**Why:**  
- Breaks static tooling (`nixd`, `nil`)  
- Hides scope/causes IDE completion failures  
- Reduces code readability

```nix
# ❌ BAD
environment.systemPackages = with pkgs; [ git vim ];
meta = with lib; { license = licenses.mit; };
# ✅ GOOD
environment.systemPackages = [ pkgs.git pkgs.vim ];
meta = { license = lib.licenses.mit; };
```

---

## ✨ Core Principles

```markdown
- Explicit > Implicit attribute paths
- Pure, declarative functional design
- Use let-in, never rec
- Format: `nixfmt-rfc-style`
- Destructure args, never use `with`
```

---

## 🔲 Flake Structure Visual

```markdown
flake.nix
├── inputs (flake-parts, nixpkgs, ...)
├── outputs:
    ├── systems = [all 4 platforms]
    ├── perSystem:
    │    ├── devShells.default    # development shell
    │    ├── packages.default     # main package/build
    └── flake.nixosConfigurations
```

```nix
{
  description = "...";
  inputs = {
    nixpkgs.url = "...";
    flake-parts.url = "...";
    home-manager = {
      url = "...";
      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = "nixpkgs";
    };
  };
  outputs = { self, nixpkgs, flake-parts, ... }@inputs:
    flake-parts.lib.mkFlake { inherit inputs; } {
      systems = [ "x86_64-linux" "aarch64-linux" "aarch64-darwin" "x86_64-darwin" ];
      perSystem = { pkgs, ... }: {
        devShells.default = pkgs.mkShell { nativeBuildInputs = [ pkgs.git ]; };
        packages.default = pkgs.hello;
      };
      flake.nixosConfigurations.myhost = nixpkgs.lib.nixosSystem { modules = [ ./configuration.nix ]; };
    };
}
```

